Senate Resolution 344
By: Senators Orrock of the 36th, Jones II of the 22nd, Jackson of the 41st, Parent of the 44th
and Islam Parkes of the 7th
A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the Senate Study Committee on a Single-payer Healthcare Program; and for other
2 purposes.
3
4 WHEREAS, the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act (ACA) was enacted by Congress
5 in 2010, fundamentally reforming the American healthcare system, by expanding Medicaid
6 to 138 percent of the federal poverty line and making various changes to the health insurance
7 industry; and
8 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia has refused to implement Medicaid expansion as
9 contemplated by the ACA, leaving nearly 300,000 Georgians uninsured; and
10 WHEREAS, most other highly developed countries, including Australia, Canada, India,
11 Israel, Italy, New Zealand, Spain, Taiwan, and the United Kingdom, have single-payer
12 healthcare systems of some kind; and
13 WHEREAS, opinion polls have shown that countries with single-payer healthcare systems
14 almost universally prefer their systems over an American-style private healthcare system;
15 and
