16 WHEREAS, various proposals have been introduced in Congress to create a nation-wide
17 single-payer healthcare system, and many states, including California, Colorado, Hawaii, and
18 Vermont, have explored the creation of a single-payer healthcare system at the state level;
19 and
20 WHEREAS, studies have shown that the United States would save approximately half a
21 trillion dollars every year under a single-payer system, and that as many as 212,000 lives
22 could have been saved during the COVID-19 pandemic; and
23 WHEREAS, the implementation of a single-payer healthcare system in Georgia would
24 significantly improve healthcare outcomes in this state; and
25 WHEREAS, a study committee is needed to establish informed recommendations for the
26 implementation of a single-payer healthcare system.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE:
28 (1) Creation of Senate study committee. There is created the Senate Study Committee
29 on a Single-payer Healthcare Program.
30 (2) Members and officers.
31 (A) The committee shall be composed of the following members:
32 (i) Five members of the Senate to be appointed by the President of the Senate;
33 (ii) The commissioner of public health or his or her designee;
34 (iii) The commissioner of community health or his or her designee; and
35 (iv) The commissioner of behavioral health and developmental disabilities or his or
36 her designee.
37 (B) The President of the Senate shall designate a legislative member of the committee
38 to be the chairperson of the committee.
