39 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs,
40 issues, and problems mentioned above or related thereto and recommend any action or
41 legislation which the committee deems necessary or appropriate.
42 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
43 may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or
44 convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and
45 accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
46 (5) Allowances and funding. The legislative members of the committee shall receive
47 the allowances provided for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia
48 Annotated. Members of the committee who are state officials, other than legislative
49 members, or who are state employees, shall receive no compensation for their services
50 on the committee, but they may be reimbursed for expenses incurred by them in the
51 performance of their duties as members of the committee in the same manner as they are
52 reimbursed for expenses in their capacities as state officials or employees. The
53 allowances authorized by this resolution shall not be received by any member of the
54 committee for more than five days unless additional days are authorized. Funds
55 necessary to carry out the provisions of this resolution shall come from funds
56 appropriated to the Senate; except that funds for the reimbursement of the expenses of
57 state officials, other than legislative members, and for the reimbursement of the expenses
58 of state employees shall come from funds appropriated to or otherwise available to their
59 respective agencies.
60 (6) Report.
61 (A) In the event the committee adopts any specific findings or recommendations that
62 include suggestions for proposed legislation, the chairperson shall file a report of the
63 same prior to the date of abolishment specified in this resolution, subject to
64 subparagraph (C) of this paragraph.
